# 4. 思いがけぬ電話

Airi: Phew... We sure did a lot today, looking at four different houses.
Minori: Yeah, and we found a really amazing house right at the end!
Haruka: Still, there's no telling whether or not we're going to get approved.
MEIKO: <You'll be meeting with the landlady at eight the evening after next for an interview, yes?>
Shizuku: I wasn't expecting to be interviewed. I'm actually a little nervous. What do you think we're going to be asked...?
Airi: Questions that show whether or not we're actually capable of making our dreams come true, right?
Minori: H-How are we supposed to clearly convey that...?
Luka: <Whatever you're asked, I think you should tell this landlady how you truly feel. Just be yourselves and say whatever comes to mind.>
Miku: <Is someone calling?>
Shizuku: Oh, it's Saito. Let me just press the speakerphone button and... Yes, hello?
Saito: <Hello! You all went to look at those houses, yes? Did you find anything nice?>
Shizuku: Yes, we found a very lovely one.
Minori: We have to get approved for it first... But you've really gotta see it, Saito!
Saito: <That's great to hear...! I really wish I could be there with you all, but the inn's just too busy right now...>
Haruka: That's more than okay. We still can't thank you enough for finding a real estate agency for us while working at your family's inn.
Airi: If we do manage to get approved, you're gonna be the first one to receive a tour! So wish us luck!
Saito: <Thank you! I feel even more motivated to do a good job here!>
Saito: <Oh, also... There's another reason why I called you.>
Saito: <The producer for iHaz, Mr. Kuromiya, just contacted me.>
Minori: Really?
Saito: <Yes, and...>
Saito: <Apparently, the idol group that was supposed to appear on one of his other shows had to cancel all of a sudden...>
Saito: <So, MORE MORE JUMP! is being asked to fill in for them.>
Haruka: Huh...?
Minori: Wait... We get to be on TV again?!
Saito: <Yes, but it's a tight schedule. The shoot for it is the day after tomorrow... How do you all feel about this?>
Saito: <You currently have nothing going on that day, but I felt that I should ask just in case.>
Minori: The day after tomorrow...
Shizuku: That's when the landlady's going to interview us.
Airi: As important as that interview is, we shouldn't let a chance like this slip by...
Haruka: I agree. And since it's one of Mr. Kuromiya's shows, it's probably going to air for one of the big networks... This is a huge opportunity for us to raise our name recognition.
Minori: B-By the way, did you hear when it might end?!
Saito: <Let's see... It's scheduled to end at three.>
Shizuku: Oh, that works out really well since our interview is at eight.
Minori: Yeah, we'd have five hours to pack up and move! That should be more than enough time!
Haruka: Then, would you mind accepting this offer on our behalf?
Saito: <Understood! Also, are you all free after this?>
Shizuku: Yes, we're free. We were actually just about to head home...
Saito: <Perfect! The thing is, the station would like to have a meeting with you right now if possible.>
Saito: <They don't seem set on it if it's too much trouble, but would you be willing to make a quick detour...?>
Minori: Of course!
Haruka: If the shoot's the day after tomorrow, we should sit down and meet with them as soon as we can.
Saito: <Wonderful! Then, I'll let the station know that you'll be dropping by soon. In the meantime, please start heading over.>
Minori: Roger! Thank you so much, Saito!
Shizuku: We'll see you later.
Len: <That's awesome. You really get to be on TV again?>
Airi: I know, right? We really can't thank Mr. Kuromiya enough. First, we got to go on iHaz, and now this.
Luka: <But you all should hurry. I'm sure the producer's eagerly awaiting your arrival.>
KAITO: <Then, we should head back to SEKAI. Tell us how things go later, okay?>
Minori: Okay! We'll talk again soon!
Haruka: Alright, we should get going. See you all later.
Rin: <Bye bye!>
Minori: Huff... Huff...
Minori: I thought it was pretty close by... But getting here took longer than I was expecting! I hope we're not making Mr. Kuromiya wait on us!
Haruka: I mean, none of us knew they were doing all that road construction...
Airi: Anyway, we gotta hurry! We just got a message saying that he'll be waiting for us at seven in the meeting room.
Minori: Seven...? Wait, that's in five minutes! Once the light turns green, we should bolt and...
???: Ah!
Minori: Huh...?
Minori: A-Are you okay?
Elderly Lady: Oh, pardon me... This is so embarrassing. I think I just broke a heel...
Haruka: Can you stand? Here, take my hand.
Elderly Lady: Thank you. You're so sweet.
Elderly Lady: ...!
Airi: ...! Is your foot hurt? Maybe your ankle?
Elderly Lady: Yes, I believe so... I may've twisted it a little just now.
Shizuku: We should find a place where you can rest. Are there any benches or...
Elderly Lady: No, no, I'll be fine. I appreciate the concern, but I should be able to make it to my destination. It's actually just right there.
Shizuku: B-But...
Minori: Then, I'll help you get there!
Elderly Lady: What...?
Minori: You guys go on ahead without me, okay? I'll be right behind you!
Airi: Okay. We'll let Mr. Kuromiya know that you're helping her.
Minori: Thanks! See you in a bit!
Elderly Lady: I'm so sorry... You and your friends also seemed to be in a hurry.
Minori: No, that's totally okay since they agreed to go on ahead without me!
Minori: Anyway, where were you headed? My hope is that you'll get a chance to rest there and...
Elderly Lady: Oh, actually, it's right there.
Minori: Where...? Wait, the TV station?
Elderly Lady: Yes... I'm here to see the shoot for a talk show.
Elderly Lady: But it'll be starting soon. Whatever shall I do...?
Minori: (She's going to be a part of the studio audience...?)
Minori: (But they probably won't let her in once the cameras start rolling. She seems so excited about it. I don't want her to miss out...)
Minori: Please let me carry you on my back!
Elderly Lady: What?
Minori: We'll be able to move faster, and you might just make it in time to see that shoot!
Minori: You sounded really excited about it, so I don't want you to miss it!
Elderly Lady: Thank you, Minori... I really appreciate you being so kind.
Minori: Again, it's okay! We were also just headed there anyway!
Minori: Okay, please hang on tight...!
Minori: Hm?
Minori: (Wait a second... When did I tell her my name?)
